{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/","type":"reference"},{"text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with ","type":"text"},{"code":"pmtiles:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be ","type":"text"},{"code":"https:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, ","type":"text"},{"code":"asset:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load an asset or ","type":"text"},{"code":"file:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to load a local PMTiles file.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"PMTiles sources currently do not support caching or offline pack downloads.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":""},{"type":"text","text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles"},{"type":"text","text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile server."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"pmtiles-demo.png","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"mod